UNESCO 's City of Literature program is part of its Creative Cities Network which was launched in 2004 .
The Network was born out of UNESCO 's Global Alliance for Cultural Diversity initiative which was created in 2002 .
Its aim is to `` promote the social , economic and cultural development of cities in both the developed and the developing world . ''
The cities in network promote their local creative scene and conform to UNESCO 's goal of fostering cultural diversity .